01:38:54,273 --> 01:38:55,554
Thank you, sir.

1203
01:39:04,951 --> 01:39:07,110
- Hey. How you doing?
- Hey.

1204
01:39:11,166 --> 01:39:14,121
So did you finish the whole thing,
or you have to go somewhere?

1205
01:39:14,336 --> 01:39:16,792
I have to go somewhere.

1206
01:39:17,381 --> 01:39:20,217
- But I finished the whole thing too.
- Oh, good.

1207
01:39:20,426 --> 01:39:22,335
- You?
- Yeah.

1208
01:39:22,845 --> 01:39:25,800
- How'd you feel about the graphs?
- Easy.

1209
01:39:26,850 --> 01:39:30,895
I struggled with the essay question
on the back. What did you write?

1210
01:39:31,104 --> 01:39:34,723
- Essay question?
- Yeah, on the back.

1211
01:39:44,660 --> 01:39:45,989
Hey, Chris.

1212
01:39:46,204 --> 01:39:49,489
- Hey. Jeff, right? 49ers game.
- Yeah.

1213
01:39:49,707 --> 01:39:53,159
- Yeah, you were gonna give me a call?
- I never actually got your number.

1214
01:39:54,921 --> 01:39:56,878
Here's my number.
Call me, okay?

1215
01:39:57,090 --> 01:39:59,760
Yes, sir. Absolutely.
Thank you very much.

1216
01:40:00,552 --> 01:40:04,301
Chris, you got five bucks?
I left my wallet upstairs.

1217
01:40:04,515 --> 01:40:06,757
Let me run up and grab that
for you, Mr. Frohm.

1218
01:40:06,976 --> 01:40:09,977
No, I gotta be at CAL Bank at 4,
and I'm late.

1219
01:40:15,359 --> 01:40:17,518
- I'll pay you back, honest.
- Five is good?

1220
01:40:17,737 --> 01:40:21,355
Five is lovely. Thank you.
Thank you.

1221
01:40:34,713 --> 01:40:37,205
That's it. That's the room quota.

1222
01:40:37,591 --> 01:40:40,343
There's no more space.
You gotta head out.

1223
01:40:40,553 --> 01:40:43,424
That's it for today.
Come back tomorrow.

1224
01:40:43,639 --> 01:40:46,641
All the rooms are full.
It's completely full.

1225
01:40:46,851 --> 01:40:51,145
That's it. Just keep heading out.
Come back tomorrow.

1226
01:41:26,143 --> 01:41:27,886
You like it?

1227
01:42:18,949 --> 01:42:22,614
Twenty. One, two, three, four.

1228
01:42:25,706 --> 01:42:29,325
Now, here's your bulb,
and there's your ferrite core inductor.

1229
01:42:29,544 --> 01:42:32,331
- How much?
- Eight dollars.

1230
01:42:33,423 --> 01:42:36,756
- What's that?
- It's to repair the light.

1231
01:42:36,968 --> 01:42:39,008
Can I see it?

1232
01:42:40,889 --> 01:42:43,973
Yeah, sure. Just don't break it.

1233
01:42:44,184 --> 01:42:48,681
Unless you wanna sleep in a room
with me for the rest of your life.

1234
01:42:49,899 --> 01:42:51,725
I don't mind.

1235
01:42:52,234 --> 01:42:54,026
Yeah, you will.

1236
01:43:10,337 --> 01:43:12,709
Why don't you
get some sleep, okay?

1237
01:43:12,923 --> 01:43:14,038
Okay.

1238
01:43:14,258 --> 01:43:17,378
- Warm enough?
- Yeah.

1239
01:43:17,636 --> 01:43:19,296
All right.

1240
01:43:21,432 --> 01:43:24,303
Did Mom leave because of me?

1241
01:43:27,647 --> 01:43:31,859
- What?
- Did Mom leave because of me?

1242
01:43:36,448 --> 01:43:40,944
Don't... Don't even think
something like that.

1243
01:43:42,037 --> 01:43:44,160
Mom left because of Mom.

1244
01:43:44,373 --> 01:43:46,615
And you didn't have anything
to do with that, okay?

1245
01:43:47,334 --> 01:43:49,244
Okay.

1246
01:43:59,097 --> 01:44:01,137
You're a good papa.

1247
01:44:08,982 --> 01:44:10,975
All right, go to sleep.

1248
01:44:11,819 --> 01:44:14,736
- I love you.
- I love you too.

1249
01:45:11,215 --> 01:45:13,172
So far, so good, Chris.

1250
01:45:19,265 --> 01:45:21,839
- It works.
- Thank you very much.

1251
01:45:22,060 --> 01:45:25,844
Two hundred and fifty dollars.
Four more weeks of oxygen.

1252
01:45:26,231 --> 01:45:30,443
One hundred, 20, 40, 60, 80, 200.

1253
01:45:30,652 --> 01:45:33,404
Twenty, 30, 40, 50.

1254
01:45:34,573 --> 01:45:36,198
- Anything else?
- Nope, that's it.

1255
01:45:36,409 --> 01:45:37,689
Thank you. Thank you.

1256
01:45:37,910 --> 01:45:39,867
- You ready?
- Yep.

1257
01:45:41,789 --> 01:45:44,707
- Are we going to the church place?
- No.

1258
01:45:44,918 --> 01:45:46,875
Where are we going, then?

1259
01:45:47,671 --> 01:45:50,209
- Probably stay at a hotel.
- A hotel?

1260
01:45:50,423 --> 01:45:51,503
Just for the night.

1261
01:45:51,717 --> 01:45:54,468
We can go back to the cave
if you like.

1262
01:45:54,678 --> 01:45:56,386
No, thank you.

1263
01:45:56,597 --> 01:45:59,135
- Ever?
- I hope not.

1264
01:45:59,350 --> 01:46:00,808
Why not?

1265
01:46:01,018 --> 01:46:03,805
Well, because some things are fun
the first time you do them...

1266
01:46:04,021 --> 01:46:06,347
...and then not so much the next.

1267
01:46:06,566 --> 01:46:09,436
- Like the bus?
- Yeah, like the bus.

1268
01:46:09,652 --> 01:46:13,104
I'm sorry. Guess I shouldn't laugh,
should I?

1269
01:46:13,323 --> 01:46:16,692
It's promised in the Bible.
Pa says we'll find it some day.

1270
01:46:16,910 --> 01:46:19,282
He doesn't know where it is, though.

1271
01:46:20,205 --> 01:46:23,408
Didn't you ever want to have a home
of your own like other people?

1272
01:46:23,625 --> 01:46:25,452
Sure.

1273
01:46:25,878 --> 01:46:27,954
Sometimes when we're moving
at night...

1274
01:46:28,172 --> 01:46:31,339
... we pass houses with lights
and people.

1275
01:46:31,550 --> 01:46:34,302
Sometimes you can
hear them laughing...

1276
01:46:38,558 --> 01:46:41,927
The next day, after work...

1277
01:46:42,145 --> 01:46:44,352
... we just went to the beach.

1278
01:46:44,564 --> 01:46:46,438
Far away from anything.

1279
01:46:46,650 --> 01:46:48,025
Everything.

1280
01:46:48,235 --> 01:46:49,895
Just Christopher and me.

1281
01:46:51,530 --> 01:46:53,902
- Did you see me?
- Yeah.

1282
01:46:54,116 --> 01:46:57,201
Far away from buses and noise...

1283
01:46:57,411 --> 01:47:03,035
... and a constant disappointment
in my ten-gallon head...

1284
01:47:04,210 --> 01:47:06,084
... and in myself.

1285
01:47:06,671 --> 01:47:09,043
- Chris, thank you very much.
- Well, thank you, Dean.

1286
01:47:09,257 --> 01:47:11,084
- Take care.
- You made all the right moves.

1287
01:47:11,301 --> 01:47:12,795
Thanks, Chris.

1288
01:47:14,888 --> 01:47:16,217
Because when I was young...

1289
01:47:16,431 --> 01:47:20,180
... and I'd get an A on a history test
or whatever...

1290
01:47:20,394 --> 01:47:24,973
... I'd get this good feeling about
all the things that I could be.

1291
01:47:26,901 --> 01:47:30,519
And then I never became
any of them.

1292
01:47:38,038 --> 01:47:40,576
- Hey, Chris.
- Hey.

1293
01:47:40,791 --> 01:47:43,412
- How you doing, Jay?
- I'm doing fine.

1294
01:47:43,627 --> 01:47:47,755
Rumour has it you signed 31 accounts
for us from Pacific Bell.

1295
01:47:47,965 --> 01:47:49,376
Yeah, yeah.

1296
01:47:49,592 --> 01:47:53,376
Met some guys at a ball game,
got some cards. I've been working.

1297
01:47:53,596 --> 01:47:55,221
I guess.

1298
01:47:58,226 --> 01:48:00,432
So one more day.

1299
01:48:00,645 --> 01:48:02,223
Getting nervous?

1300
01:48:02,814 --> 01:48:05,186
- No, I'm okay.
- Yeah?

1301
01:48:05,400 --> 01:48:07,309
Listen, whatever happens...

1302
01:48:07,527 --> 01:48:09,935
...you've done a fantastic job, Chris.

1303
01:48:10,155 --> 01:48:11,697
I mean that.

1304
01:48:12,574 --> 01:48:14,366
Take care of yourself.

1305
01:48:29,426 --> 01:48:32,546
Yes, Mr. Johnson.
Chris Gardner, Dean Witter.

1306
01:48:32,888 --> 01:48:34,964
Yes, sir. Just calling
to thank you very much...

1307
01:48:35,182 --> 01:48:37,673
...for your support
at last month's seminar.

1308
01:48:38,227 --> 01:48:39,887
Yes, sir. Absolutely.

1309
01:48:40,521 --> 01:48:42,145
Yes, sir.

1310
01:48:42,356 --> 01:48:43,731
No, sir, that's it.

1311
01:48:43,941 --> 01:48:46,397
Thank you very much. Bye-bye.

1312
01:48:48,029 --> 01:48:50,899
Chris. Come.

1313
01:49:18,311 --> 01:49:21,395
- Hi, Chris.
- Mr. Frohm, good to see you.

1314
01:49:22,524 --> 01:49:24,433
- Nice shirt.
- Thank you, sir.

1315
01:49:24,651 --> 01:49:25,849
- Chris.
- Hey, Jay.

1316
01:49:26,319 --> 01:49:30,567
- Chris.
- Chris, sit down, please.

1317
01:49:33,494 --> 01:49:37,574
I thought I'd wear a shirt today.

1318
01:49:37,790 --> 01:49:39,747
You know,
being the last day and all.

1319
01:49:39,959 --> 01:49:43,293
Well, thank you. Thank you.
We appreciate that.

1320
01:49:44,172 --> 01:49:45,963
But...

1321
01:49:46,174 --> 01:49:48,961
...wear one tomorrow though, okay?

1322
01:49:49,177 --> 01:49:52,095
Because tomorrow's
going to be your first day...

1323
01:49:52,847 --> 01:49:56,051
...if you'd like to work here
as a broker.

1324
01:49:57,394 --> 01:49:59,221
Would you like that, Chris?

1325
01:50:00,147 --> 01:50:01,725
Yes, sir.

1326
01:50:01,940 --> 01:50:05,310
Good. We couldn't be happier.

1327
01:50:06,278 --> 01:50:09,445
So welcome.

1328
01:50:11,325 --> 01:50:16,320
- Was it as easy as it looked?
- No, sir. No, sir, it wasn't.

1329
01:50:18,667 --> 01:50:21,039
- Good luck, Chris.
- Thank you. Thank you.

1330
01:50:25,465 --> 01:50:27,126
Thank you, sir.

1331
01:50:27,468 --> 01:50:29,341
Oh, Chris.

1332
01:50:31,847 --> 01:50:33,923
I almost forgot.

1333
01:50:35,977 --> 01:50:37,519
Thank you.

1334
01:50:57,917 --> 01:51:00,123
This part of my life...

1335
01:51:01,045 --> 01:51:03,203
... this little part...

1336
01:51:06,592 --> 01:51:09,214
... is called "Happiness."

1337
01:51:55,936 --> 01:51:59,555
Christopher. Christopher.
Come here.

1338
01:52:29,222 --> 01:52:31,630
So how many...

1339
01:52:31,850 --> 01:52:33,759
...planets are there?

1340
01:52:35,061 --> 01:52:36,853
- Seven.
- Seven?

1341
01:52:37,355 --> 01:52:39,182
Nine.

1342
01:52:41,568 --> 01:52:43,644
Who's the king of the jungle?

1343
01:52:44,029 --> 01:52:46,781
- Gorilla.
- The gorilla?

1344
01:52:47,074 --> 01:52:48,485
The gorilla?

1345
01:52:48,701 --> 01:52:50,325
No. Lion.

1346
01:52:50,536 --> 01:52:53,158
Oh, yeah. Lion, lion, lion.

1347
01:52:55,208 --> 01:52:58,209
Hey, Dad, listen to this.
Knock, knock.

1348
01:52:58,419 --> 01:53:00,329
- Who's there?
- Shelby.

1349
01:53:00,547 --> 01:53:01,661
Shelby who?

1350
01:53:01,881 --> 01:53:05,666
Shelby coming around the mountain
When she comes

1351
01:53:06,511 --> 01:53:07,840
- Knock knock.
- Who's there?

1352
01:53:08,055 --> 01:53:10,510
- Nobody.
- Nobody who?

1353
01:53:11,433 --> 01:53:13,177
Nobody who?

1354
01:53:16,522 --> 01:53:19,476
Now, that's funny. I like that one.

